The '''Tensor Contraction Engine (TCE)''' is a [[compiler]] for a domain-specific language that allows chemists to specify the computation in a high-level [[Wolfram Mathematica|Mathematica]]-style language. It transforms [[tensor]] summation expressions to low-level code (C/Fortran) for specific hardware being mindful of [[Computer memory|memory]] availability, communication costs, [[loop fusion]] and ordering, etc. It is used primarily in [[computational chemistry]].

